WEBVTT

00:00.913 --> 00:04.003
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12.882 --> 00:16.842
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:17.017 --> 00:20.542
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:20.716 --> 00:24.589
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.763 --> 00:27.940
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.115 --> 00:30.769
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY ♪

00:31.379 --> 00:33.859
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT ♪

00:36.993 --> 00:38.777
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY ♪

00:38.951 --> 00:42.303
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.610 --> 00:49.353
♪ I'LL BE READY
[I'LL BE READY] ♪

00:49.527 --> 00:53.314
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR
[NO DON'T YOU FEAR] ♪

00:53.488 --> 00:56.752
♪ I'LL BE READY ♪

00:56.926 --> 00:59.798
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

00:59.972 --> 01:02.845
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

01:20.732 --> 01:22.734
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY ♪

01:22.908 --> 01:26.086
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:29.698 --> 01:33.528
♪ I'LL BE READY
[I'LL BE READY] ♪

01:33.702 --> 01:37.358
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR
[NO DON'T YOU FEAR] ♪

01:37.532 --> 01:40.665
♪ I'LL BE READY ♪

01:40.839 --> 01:43.755
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

01:43.929 --> 01:47.019
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

01:47.150 --> 01:51.328
[THEME MUSIC]

02:03.645 --> 02:07.170
-I LOVE IT DOWN THERE. BE BACK
AS SOON AS I GET OUR DINNER.

02:07.301 --> 02:08.693
JUST LIKE THE OLD DAYS.

02:08.824 --> 02:09.738
-BE CAREFUL.

02:09.868 --> 02:11.479
AND HURRY BACK.

02:11.609 --> 02:15.135
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

02:53.216 --> 02:54.957
-[SCREAMING]

02:55.087 --> 03:00.136
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

03:06.229 --> 03:08.405
-[GRUNTING]

03:15.195 --> 03:16.848
HELP! HELP!

03:16.979 --> 03:20.896
MY HUSBAND'S DIVING.
I PULLED ON THE SAFETY LINE,

03:21.026 --> 03:22.593
BUT I CAN'T GET
HIM TO THE SURFACE.

03:22.724 --> 03:24.682
I'M AFRAID SOMETHING'S
SERIOUSLY WRONG.

03:25.292 --> 03:26.728
-THIS IS LIEUTENANT
STEPHANIE HOLDEN

03:26.858 --> 03:28.730
OF THE LOS ANGELES COUNTY
DEPARTMENT OF BEACHES,

03:28.860 --> 03:30.340
WHERE ARE YOU?

03:30.471 --> 03:31.950
-WOMAN: WE'RE ABOUT
THREE AND A HALF MILES

03:32.081 --> 03:34.562
NORTHWEST OF THE
PARADISE COVE PIER.

03:34.692 --> 03:36.303
-OKAY, WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

03:36.433 --> 03:37.391
HOLD ON!

03:39.697 --> 03:44.702
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

03:49.316 --> 03:50.317
-HERE!

03:52.144 --> 03:53.494
-STEPHANIE: TOSS
ME THE SPARE AIR.

03:54.625 --> 03:58.934
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

04:33.011 --> 04:35.187
-BARNETT, I NEED THE BOAT HOOK.

04:39.017 --> 04:39.888
THANKS.

04:40.802 --> 04:43.239
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

05:35.247 --> 05:37.772
-THAT LOOKS GREAT.
YOU GUYS DID A TERRIFIC JOB.

05:37.902 --> 05:40.035
-WE'LL HANG THESE POSTERS
AND PUT UP THE FLAGS.

05:40.165 --> 05:42.559
-THANKS, JOHN. NOW, LISTEN,
SOME OF YOU WILL BE WORKING

05:42.690 --> 05:44.692
WITH THE ATHLETES BUT I'LL
NEED THE REST OF YOU ON TOWERS,

05:44.822 --> 05:46.868
SO PLEASE, CHECK THE ASSIGNMENT
SHEET TOMORROW, OKAY?

05:46.998 --> 05:47.999
ALL RIGHT. LET'S GO.

05:52.264 --> 05:53.309
THANK YOU, BIFF.

05:56.007 --> 05:59.010
REMEMBER, POSTERS FROM
VENICE ALL THE WAY TO MALIBU.

06:01.883 --> 06:03.624
-DAD!
-MITCH: HOBIE.

06:03.754 --> 06:05.234
-HEY, I MADE THIS
FOR YOU IN SCHOOL.

06:07.062 --> 06:10.152
-WOW, THAT'S UNBELIEVABLE.

06:10.282 --> 06:12.546
-I KNEW YOU'D LOVE IT. I
GOTTA GO PRACTICE MUSICAL FLAGS

06:12.676 --> 06:14.156
FOR THE JUNIOR
LIFEGUARD COMPETITIONS.

06:14.286 --> 06:16.027
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.
-OKAY.

06:16.593 --> 06:19.596
NO IDEA HE WAS SO TALENTED.

06:20.118 --> 06:21.903
-OH. LOVE YOUR RING, MITCH.

06:23.165 --> 06:24.384
-ME TOO!

06:25.559 --> 06:26.603
-MITCH: COME HERE YOU!

06:28.910 --> 06:32.522
-WILL YOU PUT ME DOWN? YOU
KNOW I HATE IT WHEN YOU DO THAT.

06:34.045 --> 06:38.223
-SORRY, I COULDN'T HELP MYSELF.
YOU CARE FOR AN ARTICHOKE?

06:38.354 --> 06:39.399
-NO.

06:39.529 --> 06:41.139
IT'S SO GOOD TO SEE YOU MITCH.

06:41.270 --> 06:42.489
-GREAT TO SEE YOU TOO.

06:43.446 --> 06:46.014
THIS IS LIEUTENANT STEPHANIE
HOLDEN, MARY LOU RETTON.

06:46.144 --> 06:47.929
-OH, IT'S SO GREAT TO MEET YOU.

06:48.625 --> 06:50.148
I'LL NEVER FORGET
THE '84 OLYMPICS

06:50.279 --> 06:52.977
WHEN YOU WON ALL THOSE MEDALS.
YOU WERE AMAZING.

06:53.108 --> 06:54.414
-WELL THANK YOU.

06:55.023 --> 06:57.373
IT'S GREAT TO BE HERE,
THANKS TO MITCH'S OFFER.

06:57.504 --> 06:59.070
-ANYTHING FOR YOU.

06:59.201 --> 07:01.856
-WELL, OFFERING TO HOST
THE SPECIAL OLYMPICS

07:01.986 --> 07:04.989
ISN'T JUST ANYTHING. I MEAN,
THE BEACH AS AN OLYMPIC VENUE

07:05.120 --> 07:06.904
IS JUST WHAT THESE KIDS NEED.

07:07.035 --> 07:09.516
THEY'VE BEEN WORKING OUT SO
HARD, AND THEY REALLY DESERVE

07:09.646 --> 07:10.604
THIS CHANGE OF SCENE.

07:11.126 --> 07:12.475
I CAN'T THANK YOU ENOUGH MITCH.

07:13.084 --> 07:15.870
-JUST THE LOOK ON THEIR
FACES WILL BE THANKS ENOUGH.

07:16.566 --> 07:18.786
NOW WE'VE GOT A LOT OF PLANNING
TO DO AND STEPHANIE SAID

07:18.916 --> 07:20.614
SHE WOULD HELP COORDINATE,
SO WHY DON'T WE MEET

07:20.744 --> 07:23.312
AT MY HOUSE TONIGHT FOR
DINNER, AT EIGHT O'CLOCK, HUH?

07:23.443 --> 07:25.183
-YOU COOKING?
-MITCH: UH HUH.

07:25.314 --> 07:26.968
-I'LL BRING PIZZA.

07:27.098 --> 07:28.404
[LAUGHTER]

07:28.535 --> 07:31.320
-FUNNY. WATCH IT.

07:34.410 --> 07:36.847
ANYWAY, THIS AUDITORIUM
MUST HAVE HAD

07:36.978 --> 07:40.285
LIKE 5,000 PEOPLE IN THERE.
BUSINESS MEN,

07:40.416 --> 07:42.418
HEADS OF CORPORATIONS,
AND THEY WERE HANGING

07:42.549 --> 07:44.376
ON MARY LOU'S EVERY WORD.

07:45.421 --> 07:47.554
I'M TELLING YOU, YOU REALLY
MOTIVATED ME THAT NIGHT.

07:48.468 --> 07:50.687
-DO YOU THINK MAYBE YOU COULD
COME GIVE A TALK TO MY CLASS?

07:50.818 --> 07:53.342
-BELIEVE ME, HIS
CLASS NEEDS MOTIVATION.

07:53.473 --> 07:56.171
-I'D LOVE TO HOBIE. I MEAN,
AS MUCH AS I LOVE

07:56.301 --> 07:58.913
MY MOTIVATIONAL SPEAKING,
WORKING WITH KIDS

07:59.043 --> 08:00.915
IS MY ABSOLUTE
FAVORITE THING TO DO.

08:01.045 --> 08:02.699
-I THINK IT'S WONDERFUL
THAT YOU DEVOTE

08:02.830 --> 08:04.484
SO MUCH TIME TO
SPECIAL OLYMPICS.

08:05.223 --> 08:08.357
-OH STEPHANIE, THESE ATHLETES
HAVE SO MUCH LOVE TO GIVE.

08:08.488 --> 08:10.533
I MEAN, IT'S LIKE THEY'RE
BURSTING AT THE SEAMS.

08:11.186 --> 08:13.580
MOST OF THEM HAVE NEVER
EVEN BEEN TO A BEACH BEFORE.

08:15.190 --> 08:17.322
SAMMY SAYS THE WAVES NEVER STOP

08:17.453 --> 08:19.150
BECAUSE THEY LOVE
TO CHASE PEOPLE.

08:19.281 --> 08:20.064
-HOBIE: WHO'S SAMMY?

08:20.848 --> 08:22.153
-SAMMY'S A GYMNAST.

08:22.676 --> 08:24.765
SHE WAS ABANDONED BY HER
PARENTS WHEN SHE WAS JUST

08:24.895 --> 08:27.811
AN INFANT. THEY JUST COULDN'T
DEAL WITH HER HANDICAP,

08:27.942 --> 08:30.422
SO SHE'S NEVER HAD THE
SUPPORT OF A FAMILY,

08:30.553 --> 08:32.729
AND SHE REALLY NEEDS
SOME SPECIAL ATTENTION.

08:34.034 --> 08:37.342
YOU KNOW, STEPHANIE, I THINK
YOUR INFLUENCE COULD REALLY

08:37.472 --> 08:38.953
MAKE A DIFFERENCE FOR SAMMY.

08:39.082 --> 08:41.042
DO YOU THINK YOU COULD
SPEND SOME TIME WITH HER?

08:43.087 --> 08:45.394
-WELL OF COURSE, ABSOLUTELY.

08:46.047 --> 08:47.962
I'D LOVE TO HELP
HER ANY WAY I CAN.

08:48.092 --> 08:49.050
-GREAT.

08:50.486 --> 08:51.748
-HOBIE, YOU WANNA
HELP CLEAN UP?

08:51.879 --> 08:53.184
-YEAH.
-MITCH.

08:53.315 --> 08:54.316
-MITCH: YES?

08:55.099 --> 08:58.363
-YOU'VE DONE SO MUCH ALREADY.
I HATE TO ASK MORE.

08:58.494 --> 09:00.714
-BUT I GET THE FEELING
YOU'RE GOING TO.

09:02.019 --> 09:03.499
STEP INTO MY OFFICE.

09:11.594 --> 09:12.682
WHAT'S UP?

09:13.814 --> 09:17.687
-THERE'S THIS YOUNG MAN, DARNEL.
HE WAS INSTITUTIONALIZED,

09:17.818 --> 09:18.906
AND HE SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN.

09:19.950 --> 09:21.778
HIS FATHER GAVE HIM
UP WHEN HE WAS SMALL

09:21.909 --> 09:24.128
AND DARNEL'S NEVER
GOTTEN OVER IT.

09:24.825 --> 09:27.741
MITCH, HE POURS HIMSELF
INTO THESE COMPETITIONS,

09:27.871 --> 09:29.481
MAYBE A LITTLE TOO MUCH.

09:30.657 --> 09:34.486
-SO YOU WANT ME TO MAYBE
TAKE DARNEL UNDER MY WING?

09:34.617 --> 09:35.705
-YES I DO.

09:36.619 --> 09:38.534
-ALL RIGHT. DON'T WORRY. I'LL
DO WHAT I CAN TO HELP HIM.

09:39.100 --> 09:40.101
-OH THANK YOU.

09:40.231 --> 09:42.364
-DARNEL AND SAMMY, BELIEVE ME,

09:42.494 --> 09:44.322
THEY WILL NEVER
HAVE A BETTER DAY.

09:44.975 --> 09:46.107
-GREAT.

09:49.284 --> 09:54.115
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

10:32.588 --> 10:34.198
-HI, MY NAME'S STEPHANIE.

10:36.244 --> 10:37.898
WOULD YOU LIKE TO COME
TO THE BEACH WITH ME?

10:42.903 --> 10:44.513
WELL THE SAND FEELS
REALLY GOOD ON YOUR FEET.

10:48.604 --> 10:49.474
COME ON.

11:29.950 --> 11:31.647
-HOW WE ALL DOING TODAY?

11:31.778 --> 11:34.389
-[CHEERING]

11:35.956 --> 11:37.348
-ARE WE READY TO GET PHYSICAL?

11:37.479 --> 11:39.829
-[CHEERING]

11:40.743 --> 11:43.006
-LISTEN, I AM SO GLAD
YOU'RE ALL HERE.

11:43.137 --> 11:45.226
WE READY TO TRAIN,
AND TRAIN HARD

11:45.356 --> 11:46.444
FOR THE SPECIAL OLYMPICS?

11:46.575 --> 11:47.489
-[CHEERING]

11:47.619 --> 11:49.186
-ARE WE READY TO WORK OUT?

11:49.317 --> 11:50.666
-[CHEERING]

11:50.797 --> 11:52.363
-I AM SO GLAD.

11:52.973 --> 11:54.278
MITCH, MITCH, COME HERE.

11:55.497 --> 11:59.370
EVERYONE I WANT YOU TO MEET
LIEUTENANT MITCH BUCHANNON.

11:59.501 --> 12:03.592
HE HAS BEEN KIND ENOUGH TO
OFFER US THIS BEAUTIFUL BEACH

12:03.723 --> 12:06.160
AND THE HELP OF ALL OF
THESE WONDERFUL LIFEGUARDS

12:06.290 --> 12:08.205
FOR OUR SPECIAL BEACH EVENTS.

12:08.336 --> 12:10.555
-[CHEERING]

12:12.383 --> 12:16.213
-ALL RIGHT, FIRST OF ALL,
WELCOME TO BAYWATCH.

12:16.344 --> 12:19.216
THIS IS THE VERY FIRST TIME
WE'VE HAD THE SPECIAL OLYMPICS

12:19.347 --> 12:21.262
AT THE BEACH, SO I'M COUNTING ON

12:21.392 --> 12:23.699
EACH AND EVERY ONE OF YOU, OKAY?

12:23.830 --> 12:26.876
-[CHEERING]

12:27.007 --> 12:29.836
-LISTEN, I KNOW YOU'RE
ALL ANXIOUS TO START,

12:29.966 --> 12:31.446
SO LET'S BREAK UP
INTO YOUR BUDDY GROUPS

12:31.576 --> 12:32.795
AND WE'LL HEAD
DOWN TO THE WATER.

12:32.926 --> 12:35.798
-[GENTLE MUSIC]
-[CROWD MURMURINGS]

13:11.834 --> 13:13.575
-I DON'T HAVE A PARTNER.

13:14.445 --> 13:16.317
-MITCH, THIS IS DARNEL.

13:17.448 --> 13:19.755
-DARNEL, IS IT OKAY
IF I'M YOUR PARTNER?

13:19.886 --> 13:21.235
-YEAH, SURE.

13:21.844 --> 13:24.064
-LET'S GO.
ALL RIGHT.

13:30.287 --> 13:35.292
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

13:54.790 --> 14:00.622
♪ NOW THIS FATE
THAT YOU HAVE BEEN GIVEN ♪

14:00.796 --> 14:03.712
♪ CANNOT DEFINE YOU ♪

14:03.886 --> 14:07.063
♪ IT WILL NOT CONFINE YOU ♪

14:07.716 --> 14:13.504
♪ CAUSE THIS LIFE
THAT YOU HAVE BEEN LIVIN' ♪

14:13.678 --> 14:16.812
♪ LOOKS LIKE IT'S BRAND NEW ♪

14:16.986 --> 14:22.078
♪ SHINING IN YOU ♪

14:22.949 --> 14:27.692
♪ WHEN THE CLOUDS OPEN OVER YOU ♪

14:29.129 --> 14:34.134
♪ WE ALL SEE A BRIGHTER DAY ♪

14:35.831 --> 14:40.140
♪ IT'S YOUR LIGHT
THAT IS BREAKING THROUGH ♪

14:41.097 --> 14:46.494
♪ AND TOGETHER WE'RE FINDING OUR WAY ♪

14:46.668 --> 14:51.891
♪ THE BEST IS STILL IN YOU ♪

15:06.688 --> 15:09.169
♪ NA NA NA NA NA ♪

15:13.260 --> 15:15.958
♪ NA NA NA NA NA ♪

15:19.614 --> 15:22.878
♪ NA NA NA NA NA ♪

15:25.925 --> 15:29.232
♪ THE BEST IS STILL IN YOU ♪

15:32.714 --> 15:35.804
♪ NA NA NA NA NA ♪

15:39.068 --> 15:43.420
♪ NA NA NA NA NA ♪

15:48.512 --> 15:53.822
♪ THE BEST IS STILL IN YOU ♪

16:05.268 --> 16:07.096
-OH, LET'S GO WATCH MARY
LOU ON THE BALANCE BEAM,

16:07.227 --> 16:08.054
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

16:56.537 --> 16:58.321
-WHO WANTS TO TRY?

17:01.498 --> 17:03.109
-I HEARD YOU WERE
A GYMNAST, SAMMY.

17:03.718 --> 17:05.023
WHY DIDN'T YOU PUT UP YOUR HAND?

17:05.894 --> 17:08.114
-I'M NOT GOOD ENOUGH.

17:09.593 --> 17:14.032
-OH. WELL THEN, I GUESS
WE'LL HAVE TO WORK TOGETHER

17:14.163 --> 17:15.251
UNTIL YOU DO GET GOOD ENOUGH.

17:17.210 --> 17:19.125
-DO YOU DO ANY GYMNASTICS?

17:19.255 --> 17:20.821
-RUNNING IS MY SPORT.
-REALLY?

17:20.952 --> 17:22.214
I'M THE BEST RUNNER.

17:22.345 --> 17:23.651
-NO KIDDING? HOW
LONG YOU BEEN RUNNING?

17:23.781 --> 17:25.653
-EVER SINCE I WAS A LITTLE BOY.

17:25.782 --> 17:28.569
MY FATHER SAYS I SHOULD
BE FAST AT SOMETHING

17:28.699 --> 17:31.833
'CAUSE I WAS SLOW
AT EVERYTHING ELSE.

17:33.530 --> 17:35.750
-I KNOW YOUR FATHER
LOVES YOU VERY MUCH.

17:36.707 --> 17:37.926
-YOU KNOW MY FATHER?

17:38.057 --> 17:41.277
-UH, NO. NO I DON'T,

17:41.973 --> 17:44.019
BUT I WOULD LIKE TO
GET TO KNOW YOU BETTER.

17:44.150 --> 17:46.239
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE TAKE A
RUN AND A WORKOUT TOGETHER?

17:47.414 --> 17:49.285
-JUST YOU AND ME?

17:49.416 --> 17:51.026
-JUST YOU AND ME.

17:51.157 --> 17:52.549
-WOW.

17:53.898 --> 17:56.249
-ON THREE, I'LL RACE YOU.
ONE, TWO, THREE, GO!

18:00.949 --> 18:06.172
[GRUNTING]

18:06.302 --> 18:08.565
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, HEY, HEY, HEY.

18:09.610 --> 18:11.264
WHY DON'T WE TAKE A BREAK, HUH?

18:12.569 --> 18:14.876
-BUT I GOTTA WORK OUT
SO I'LL BE THE WINNER

18:15.006 --> 18:16.617
AND YOU'LL BE PROUD OF ME.

18:17.226 --> 18:18.923
-DARNEL, I'M PROUD OF YOU NOW.

18:19.881 --> 18:22.101
AS A MATTER OF FACT, I'VE
GOT SOMETHING FOR YOU.

18:23.667 --> 18:25.800
READY? HERE WE GO.

18:28.194 --> 18:31.197
-WHOA! WHAT IS THAT?

18:31.327 --> 18:33.503
-THIS IS A FRIENDSHIP BRACELET.

18:36.158 --> 18:39.292
ONE FRIEND PUTS IT ON THE
WRIST OF ANOTHER FRIEND.

18:42.077 --> 18:43.252
PROUD TO BE YOUR FRIEND, DARNEL.

18:44.210 --> 18:46.037
YOU'RE ALREADY A WINNER WITH ME.

18:47.778 --> 18:49.215
-I WISH YOU WERE MY FATHER.

18:52.174 --> 18:54.655
-WELL I CAN'T BE YOUR FATHER,

18:55.830 --> 18:59.138
BUT I WILL ALWAYS
BE YOUR FRIEND.

19:00.922 --> 19:01.923
[KNOCKING]

19:02.053 --> 19:03.968
-HEY GUYS, HOW'S IT GOING?

19:04.839 --> 19:06.101
-HEY, HOW YOU DOING?

19:06.232 --> 19:07.058
-GOOD.

19:08.016 --> 19:09.713
-LOOK AT WHAT MITCH GOT ME.

19:09.844 --> 19:11.976
IT'S A FRIENDSHIP BRACELET.

19:12.107 --> 19:13.848
-THAT'S AWESOME.

19:13.978 --> 19:14.849
-AWESOME.

19:15.589 --> 19:17.199
-LISTEN, DARNEL, THEY'RE
PRACTICING FRISBEE

19:17.330 --> 19:18.722
OUT ON THE BEACH, WHY DON'T YOU

19:18.853 --> 19:20.071
GO OUT THERE AND SHOW
'EM HOW IT'S DONE.

19:20.202 --> 19:21.029
-YOU BET YA.

19:21.160 --> 19:22.944
COME ON, LET'S GO.

19:23.074 --> 19:25.076
-NO, NO, NO. I'M GONNA STAY
HERE AND PACK SOME THINGS UP,

19:25.207 --> 19:26.643
BUT I'LL CATCH UP
WITH YOU LATER, OKAY?

19:26.774 --> 19:28.819
-OKAY, FRIEND.

19:28.950 --> 19:29.994
-FRIEND.

19:31.735 --> 19:32.606
SEE YA.

19:34.085 --> 19:36.131
UH OH, I'VE SEEN THAT
EXPRESSION BEFORE

19:36.262 --> 19:37.350
WHEN YOU MISSED A VAULT.

19:39.221 --> 19:41.005
-COACH OF THE BOY THAT
DARNEL KNOCKED DOWN

19:41.136 --> 19:43.225
ON THE RELAY YESTERDAY
HAS LODGED A COMPLAINT.

19:43.356 --> 19:44.574
-OH NO.

19:44.705 --> 19:46.272
-AND NOW I HAVE
TO DECIDE WHETHER OR NOT

19:46.402 --> 19:48.012
TO TAKE DARNEL OUT
OF THE COMPETITION.

19:48.752 --> 19:50.276
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

19:50.406 --> 19:53.192
-LOOK, I KNOW DARNEL'S
A LITTLE TOO AGGRESSIVE,

19:53.322 --> 19:55.803
BUT IT'S ONLY BECAUSE HE
WANTS TO WIN SO BADLY.

19:56.456 --> 19:58.371
I DON'T THINK DISQUALIFYING
HIM IS THE ANSWER.

19:58.501 --> 20:00.155
-I KNOW. I WANT HIM TO COMPETE.

20:00.286 --> 20:02.288
I MEAN ESPECIALLY TOMORROW.

20:02.418 --> 20:03.985
-WHY ESPECIALLY TOMORROW?

20:04.115 --> 20:06.074
-DARNEL'S FATHER'S COMING.

20:06.205 --> 20:08.859
IT TOOK A LOT OF TIME
TO TRACK HIM DOWN

20:08.990 --> 20:10.861
AND EVEN MORE TO
CONVINCE HIM TO COME.

20:11.514 --> 20:14.735
I JUST DON'T WANT THIS DAY TO
BE RUINED FOR EITHER OF THEM.

20:16.650 --> 20:18.869
-ALL RIGHT, TELL YOU WHAT?
YOU TALK TO THE BOY'S COACH,

20:19.827 --> 20:20.784
I'LL TALK TO DARNEL.

20:20.915 --> 20:22.308
-THANKS MITCH.

20:25.136 --> 20:26.486
-GREAT, YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

20:26.616 --> 20:30.838
[PANTING]

20:30.968 --> 20:32.448
WE DON'T HAVE TOO MUCH FARTHER.

20:35.016 --> 20:37.279
OKAY, HOLD MY HAND WHILE WE
GO AROUND THE FRISBEE PLAYERS.
OKAY?

20:56.516 --> 20:58.822
-HEY, DID YOU SEE
HOW FAR I THREW THAT?

20:58.953 --> 21:01.042
-UNBELIEVABLE, THAT
THING WENT INTO ORBIT.

21:01.172 --> 21:02.478
-YEAH.

21:04.175 --> 21:05.525
-DARNEL, WHAT DO
YOU SAY YOU AND ME

21:05.655 --> 21:06.917
GO FOR A LITTLE WALK, HUH?

21:07.048 --> 21:07.918
-SURE.

21:13.576 --> 21:15.099
THE BEACH IS BEAUTIFUL.

21:15.230 --> 21:16.884
I NEVER COME HERE BEFORE.

21:19.103 --> 21:22.585
-DARNEL, I'M GONNA
EXPLAIN SOMETHING TO YOU

21:22.716 --> 21:25.284
AND I WANT YOU TO DO YOUR BEST
TO TRY AND UNDERSTAND, OKAY?

21:25.414 --> 21:26.720
-OKAY MITCH.

21:27.851 --> 21:31.377
-I KNOW WINNING IS
VERY VERY IMPORTANT TO YOU,

21:32.378 --> 21:35.206
BUT IT'S NOT AS IMPORTANT
AS DOING WHAT'S RIGHT.

21:37.992 --> 21:41.822
IN THE RELAY YESTERDAY YOU
KNOCKED DOWN ANOTHER RUNNER

21:41.952 --> 21:42.997
JUST SO YOU COULD WIN.

21:46.479 --> 21:47.784
-YOU'RE MAD AT ME.

21:47.915 --> 21:49.960
YOU WANT YOUR FRIENDSHIP
BRACELET BACK?

21:50.091 --> 21:53.050
-NO, NO, THIS HAS GOT NOTHING
TO DO WITH FRIENDSHIPS.

21:54.269 --> 21:56.837
IT'S JUST THAT THE COACH OF
THE BOY YOU KNOCKED DOWN,

21:57.838 --> 22:00.231
HE DOESN'T WANT YOU TO COMPETE
IN THE EVENTS TOMORROW.

22:02.582 --> 22:03.409
-NOT RUN?

22:04.671 --> 22:07.543
-IF MARY LOU CAN
CONVINCE THE COACH

22:07.674 --> 22:09.545
THAT YOU'LL IMPROVE
YOUR SPORTSMANSHIP,

22:10.372 --> 22:12.505
HE MAY LET YOU RUN, OKAY?

22:12.635 --> 22:14.898
-OKAY.
-OKAY.

22:16.900 --> 22:19.512
YOU KNOW, PAL, WINNING
ISN'T EVERYTHING.

22:20.034 --> 22:23.211
MY DAD ONCE TOLD ME, IT'S
NOT WHETHER YOU WIN OR LOSE,

22:23.342 --> 22:24.908
BUT IT'S HOW YOU PLAY THE GAME.

22:25.909 --> 22:28.216
SOMETIMES IT TAKES A LOT MORE
COURAGE TO DO WHAT'S RIGHT,

22:28.999 --> 22:30.349
EVEN THOUGH YOU MAY NOT WIN.

22:31.698 --> 22:35.658
-IT'S LIKE THE
SPECIAL OLYMPICS OATH.

22:38.531 --> 22:42.448
"LET ME WIN, BUT
IF I CANNOT WIN,

22:44.014 --> 22:47.409
"LET ME BE BRAVE
IN THE ATTEMPT."

22:48.454 --> 22:51.326
-EXACTLY LIKE THE
SPECIAL OLYMPICS OATH.

22:52.414 --> 22:54.416
NOW, LET'S GO! I'M
GONNA TEACH YOU

22:54.547 --> 22:56.549
HOW TO MAKE THAT FRISBEE FLY.

22:56.679 --> 22:57.767
COME ON, RACE YA.

22:58.420 --> 23:00.988
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

23:19.093 --> 23:20.094
-STEPHANIE: GOOD.

23:22.792 --> 23:24.054
OKAY, WHOA.

23:25.012 --> 23:28.189
WHOA!
OH, YOU WERE DOING TERRIFIC.

23:29.408 --> 23:30.670
-I CAN'T DO THIS.

23:31.235 --> 23:33.542
-OH, YES, YOU CAN. YOU JUST LOST
YOUR BALANCE, THAT'S ALL.

23:33.673 --> 23:36.066
-NO, I CAN'T.

23:36.197 --> 23:39.243
I CAN'T DO THIS. I QUIT.

23:39.896 --> 23:41.637
-SAMMY, SAMMY. WAIT. WAIT.

23:42.638 --> 23:44.814
I'M GONNA PROVE TO YOU
THAT YOU CAN DO THIS.

23:44.945 --> 23:46.599
I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU QUIT.

23:46.729 --> 23:47.861
OKAY?

23:49.558 --> 23:52.822
LET'S TAKE A BREAK. COME ON.

23:57.131 --> 23:59.438
-I'M SO GLAD YOU'RE HERE.
I WANNA INTRODUCE YOU

23:59.568 --> 24:01.352
TO SOMEONE REALLY
REALLY SPECIAL.

24:02.136 --> 24:03.529
-BE VERY CAREFUL WITH THE KIDS,

24:03.659 --> 24:05.182
ALTHOUGH THEY'VE GOT
A GREAT ATTITUDE, OKAY?

24:05.313 --> 24:06.532
EACH ONE WILL BE
ASSIGNED TO A CHILD.

24:06.662 --> 24:08.664
GET THE ASSIGNMENTS
FROM CJ, OKAY?

24:08.795 --> 24:09.883
-EXCUSE ME MITCH.

24:10.492 --> 24:13.147
I WANT YOU TO MEET CARL
SHEPHERD, DARNEL'S FATHER.

24:13.277 --> 24:14.627
-HI, HOW ARE YOU?

24:15.845 --> 24:16.803
OKAY, THAT'S IT.

24:20.546 --> 24:21.460
SIT DOWN, PLEASE.

24:24.637 --> 24:26.029
MR. SHEPHERD, FIRST OF ALL,

24:26.160 --> 24:28.118
THANK YOU FOR COMING
TO THE COMPETITION.

24:28.249 --> 24:30.077
I KNOW THAT YOUR SON, DARNEL,

24:30.207 --> 24:32.209
IS GOING TO BE THRILLED
THAT YOU'RE HERE.

24:33.646 --> 24:35.125
-HE DOESN'T KNOW
I'M HERE, DOES HE?

24:36.910 --> 24:38.868
-UH NO, NO NOT YET.

24:40.609 --> 24:45.135
-LOOK, TO TELL YOU
THE TRUTH, I DON'T KNOW

24:45.266 --> 24:46.963
HOW HE'S GONNA FEEL
ABOUT ME BEING HERE.

24:47.094 --> 24:49.966
I MEAN, I'M NOT QUITE SURE
HOW I FEEL ABOUT BEING HERE.

24:51.011 --> 24:53.404
SEE, I'VE NEVER BEEN ABLE TO
GIVE DARNEL WHAT HE NEEDS.

24:53.535 --> 24:57.408
-YOU KNOW, YOUR SON, HE'S
A GREAT KID, MR. SHEPHERD.

24:58.192 --> 25:01.021
HE JUST NEEDS WHAT ALL
KIDS NEED: TO BE WANTED.

25:03.240 --> 25:04.328
TO BE LOVED.

25:05.852 --> 25:08.463
-DARNEL WAS ALMOST ELIMINATED
FROM THE COMPETITION

25:08.594 --> 25:12.249
FOR KNOCKING AN OPPONENT DOWN,
BUT MITCH TALKED TO DARNEL

25:12.380 --> 25:15.339
AND I TALKED TO THE BOY'S COACH,
AND WE DECIDED

25:15.470 --> 25:18.038
TO LET HIM STAY, BECAUSE
WE BELIEVE IN HIM.

25:18.908 --> 25:19.866
-SO WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

25:19.996 --> 25:20.823
THAT I DON'T BELIEVE IN HIM?

25:20.954 --> 25:21.911
THAT I NEVER HAVE?

25:22.042 --> 25:23.043
IS THAT WHAT YOU'RE SAYING?

25:24.958 --> 25:27.830
WELL YOU'RE RIGHT. YOU'RE RIGHT.

25:29.397 --> 25:30.572
YOU KNOW I WOULDN'T BLAME DARNEL

25:30.703 --> 25:31.878
IF HE NEVER WANTED
TO SEE ME AGAIN.

25:33.401 --> 25:35.055
-MAYBE HE HASN'T
GIVEN UP ON YOU.

25:36.796 --> 25:40.974
-LOOK, I STARTED
A WHOLE NEW LIFE.

25:41.888 --> 25:43.672
I MEAN I OWN MY
OWN BUSINESS NOW.

25:44.325 --> 25:46.240
I'VE GOT A WHOLE NEW FAMILY.

25:47.284 --> 25:52.463
MY WIFE DOESN'T KNOW--
THEY DON'T KNOW ABOUT DARNEL.

25:56.772 --> 25:59.993
LOOK, THIS IS A BIG MISTAKE.
I'M SORRY. I DON'T BELONG HERE.

26:00.123 --> 26:01.385
-MR. SHEPHERD, WAIT.

26:02.256 --> 26:05.346
LISTEN, I UNDERSTAND
YOUR FEARS, AND I KNOW

26:05.476 --> 26:08.436
YOU RESENT ME DRAGGING
YOU HERE, BUT YOU CAME.

26:09.306 --> 26:10.307
-I'M SORRY.

26:12.483 --> 26:13.876
-MITCH: MR. SHEPHERD.

26:17.358 --> 26:18.881
GIVE YOUR SON A CHANCE, WILL YA?

26:20.448 --> 26:22.189
JUST GIVE HIM A
CHANCE TO LOVE YOU.

26:24.887 --> 26:29.588
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

26:33.592 --> 26:38.597
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

26:40.337 --> 26:44.820
-[GIGGLING]

27:02.142 --> 27:03.796
-I KNEW YOU COULD
BEAT THOSE WAVES.

27:03.926 --> 27:05.493
YOU'RE TOO FAST.
THEY COULDN'T CATCH YOU.

27:05.624 --> 27:07.713
-I NEVER THOUGHT I COULD DO IT.

27:07.843 --> 27:09.366
-OF COURSE YOU CAN SAMMY,

27:09.497 --> 27:11.412
YOU JUST HAVE TO
BELIEVE IN YOURSELF.

27:16.635 --> 27:18.158
I KNOW YOUR PARENTS LEFT YOU,

27:19.681 --> 27:21.465
AND I KNOW HOW LONELY THAT IS.

27:26.949 --> 27:28.429
THE SAME THING HAPPENED TO ME.

27:30.823 --> 27:31.824
-IT DID?

27:36.567 --> 27:38.526
WHO TOOK CARE OF YOU?

27:41.485 --> 27:43.487
-I WENT TO LIVE
WITH MY GRANDMOTHER.

27:45.315 --> 27:46.752
SHE DID THE BEST SHE COULD,

27:46.882 --> 27:51.408
BUT BASICALLY, I JUST
TOOK CARE OF MYSELF.

27:52.583 --> 27:54.107
I LEARNED TO BE
THERE FOR MYSELF.

27:56.979 --> 27:58.851
I GUESS I BECAME
MY OWN BEST FRIEND.

28:03.899 --> 28:07.294
-I CAN'T TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

28:08.512 --> 28:09.862
-OH YES YOU CAN.

28:11.385 --> 28:13.430
YOU CAN TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF
BY BELIEVING IN YOURSELF

28:13.561 --> 28:15.694
SAMMY, BY LOVING YOURSELF.

28:18.131 --> 28:20.611
THERE'S A LITTLE
CHILD INSIDE ALL OF US

28:20.742 --> 28:23.049
AND THAT LITTLE CHILD
NEEDS TO BE TAKEN CARE OF.

28:28.794 --> 28:31.448
SHE DIDN'T GET HUGGED A LOT
WHEN SHE WAS A LITTLE GIRL.

28:35.365 --> 28:37.193
BUT YOU CAN HUG HER
ALL THE TIME NOW.

28:40.588 --> 28:42.677
-[SCREAMING]

28:42.808 --> 28:44.853
-IT GOT US! I CAN'T
BELIEVE IT GOT US!

28:48.727 --> 28:53.732
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

28:54.820 --> 28:55.734
-RUN!

29:02.001 --> 29:04.046
-IS EVERYBODY HAPPY?

29:05.874 --> 29:07.963
I CAN'T HEAR YOU.
IS EVERYBODY HAPPY?

29:08.094 --> 29:12.054
ALL RIGHT! MY NAME IS
LIEUTENANT MITCH BUCHANNON,

29:12.185 --> 29:13.926
AND I AM VERY PROUD
TO WELCOME YOU

29:14.056 --> 29:16.058
TO THE CALIFORNIA
SPECIAL OLYMPICS.

29:16.189 --> 29:18.321
THE VERY FIRST SPECIAL OLYMPICS

29:18.452 --> 29:20.671
TO BE HELD RIGHT
HERE ON THIS BEACH.

29:24.675 --> 29:29.419
ALL RIGHT! NOW, WILL YOU PLEASE
WELCOME A VERY

29:30.072 --> 29:31.770
VERY LOVELY LADY,

29:32.727 --> 29:34.511
WHO IS GOING TO OPEN
THE GAMES FOR US.

29:35.643 --> 29:40.996
SHE WON FIVE, COUNT THEM, FIVE
MEDALS IN THE 1984 OLYMPICS.

29:41.692 --> 29:45.435
WILL YOU PLEASE WELCOME,
AND I MEAN WELCOME,

29:46.132 --> 29:48.961
THE PERFECT TEN,
MARY LOU RETTON.

29:49.091 --> 29:52.051
-[CHEERING]

29:58.448 --> 29:59.623
-THANKS MITCH.

30:00.276 --> 30:02.278
ARE YOU GUYS EXCITED TO BE HERE?

30:02.409 --> 30:05.542
-[CHEERING]

30:05.673 --> 30:07.893
-I TELL YOU WHAT, IT'S AN
HONOR FOR ME TO BE HERE,

30:08.023 --> 30:11.374
AND I ALSO WANT TO
WELCOME EVERY ONE OF YOU

30:11.505 --> 30:13.420
SPECIAL OLYMPIC
ATHLETES HERE TODAY

30:13.550 --> 30:15.465
FOR THIS TERRIFIC COMPETITION.

30:16.292 --> 30:18.642
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THE SPECIAL
OLYMPICS WERE BUILT FOR?

30:18.773 --> 30:20.383
-CROWD: NO.

30:21.036 --> 30:23.169
-THEY WERE CREATED
TO BUILD LOVE,

30:24.083 --> 30:27.390
TO BUILD JOY, TO BUILD PRIDE,

30:27.956 --> 30:30.263
AND ACCOMPLISHMENT
IN YOU, OUR ATHLETES,

30:30.959 --> 30:32.961
THROUGH THIS VERY
SPECIAL SPORTS PROGRAM.

30:33.483 --> 30:37.531
EVERY ONE OF YOU HERE
TODAY DESERVES THE CHANCE

30:37.661 --> 30:39.446
TO BE THE BEST THAT YOU CAN BE.

30:40.795 --> 30:43.189
NOW, I KNOW THAT YOU'VE
TRAINED HARD. I KNOW.

30:43.319 --> 30:46.583
I'VE SEEN YOU. YOU WERE
WORKING OUT, AND I WANT YOU

30:46.714 --> 30:49.282
TO KNOW THAT I'M PROUD OF
EACH AND EVERY ONE OF YOU.

30:51.066 --> 30:54.156
I KNOW YOU'RE
ANXIOUS TO START, SO,

30:54.940 --> 30:57.072
LET THE GAMES BEGIN!

30:57.203 --> 30:59.118
-[CHEERING]

31:04.166 --> 31:09.302
-[UPLIFTING MUSIC]

31:32.064 --> 31:33.848
-YOU'RE GONNA BE GREAT.

31:33.979 --> 31:34.762
-I HOPE SO.

31:34.893 --> 31:36.503
-I KNOW YOU WILL.

31:36.633 --> 31:37.896
I'M GONNA BE THERE WATCHING
YOU, CHEERING YOU ON.

31:39.071 --> 31:39.854
GOOD LUCK.

31:39.985 --> 31:41.508
-THANKS, STEPHANIE.

31:43.771 --> 31:48.515
-♪ NEVER LET THEM TELL
YOU THAT YOU DON'T BELONG ♪

31:50.821 --> 31:56.131
♪ YOU FEEL SO STRANGE
AND OUT OF PLACE ♪

31:57.480 --> 32:03.269
♪ HEAVEN KNOWS HEROES
ARE MADE NOT BORN ♪

32:03.965 --> 32:09.275
♪ WHEN YOU'RE RUNNING
THE HUMAN RACE ♪

32:11.320 --> 32:14.367
♪ IF THE ODDS ARE
ALL AGAINST YOU ♪

32:14.541 --> 32:17.239
♪ REACH OUT FOR MY HAND ♪

32:18.501 --> 32:21.287
♪ THERE'S SOMEONE
RIGHT BESIDE YOU ♪

32:21.461 --> 32:24.507
♪ TO HELP YOU MAKE A STAND ♪

32:25.334 --> 32:28.163
♪ ALL THE CHILD INSIDE ♪

32:28.337 --> 32:31.862
♪ LIGHT THE TORCH
